# Conventional Commits

- **Commits**: use **only** the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format.

Format:

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

## Common types

| Type     | Usage                          |
|----------|------------------------------|
| `feat`   | New feature          |
| `fix`    | Bug fix              |
| `docs`   | Documentation only          |
| `style`  | Formatting (no logic change)|
| `refactor` | Refactor (no feat/fix) |
| `test`   | Tests                       |
| `chore`  | Build, CI, deps, etc.        |

## Examples

```
feat(web): add dark mode toggle
fix(api): handle empty history on import
docs: update development setup
test(api): add server-info integration tests
chore(deps): bump eslint to 9.x
```

- `scope` is optional; use when it makes sense (e.g.: `api`, `web`, `electron`).
- For breaking change: `feat(api)!: remove legacy endpoint` or footer `BREAKING CHANGE: ...`.
- Description in lowercase, no period at the end; use imperative mood: "add" not "adds" or "added".
